Hypothesis

From this data set I chose variables:
- absenses
- health
- failures
- reason

  1. Hypothesis of absences: H0: High absences are related to high alcohol consumption H1: More absences arent related to high alcohol consumption

  2. Hypothesis of health: H0: Poor health is related to high alcohol consumption H1: Poor health isnt related to high alcohol consumption

  3. Hypothesis of failures: H0: More failures are related to high alcohol consumption H1: Failures arent related to high alcohol consumption

  4. Hypothesis of activities: H0: No activities is related to high alcohol consumption H1: Activities are related to high alcohol consumption

Absenses: I divided absences to logical type variable absences_high that is true if student have more than three absences (3.00 is the median value for absences).
